"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_N_E=self.webpackChunk_N_E||[]).push([[50],{5050:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"es":[{"id":"cuento-infinito","className":"cuento-infinito","bannerTitle1":"Lanzamiento","bannerTitle2":"del Cuento Infinito","bannerSubtitle":"Por la Minga Mundial por el Ambiente y el D\xeda de la Tierra","hasBannerButton":true,"bannerButtonText":"Reg\xedstrate aqu\xed","images":["/news/cuento-infinito/img1.png"],"date":"25 de abril, 2025","articleTitle":"Lanzamiento del Cuento Infinito ✨","articleParagraphs":["En Arcandina estamos convencidos de que los sue\xf1os de ni\xf1as y ni\xf1os tienen el poder de inspirar al mundo. Por eso, en el marco de la Minga Mundial por el Ambiente, lanzamos con much\xedsima alegr\xeda el Cuento Infinito, Arcandina El Llamado de la Vida.","\uD83D\uDCAB Un cuento colectivo, sin final, que nace inspirado en las historias de Arcandina y que contin\xfaa con las historias creadas por ni\xf1os, ni\xf1as y familias de todo el mundo que quieren contar c\xf3mo cuidan la naturaleza, siembran agua, y defienden la vida.","Para celebrar el D\xeda de la Tierra, abrimos una semana entera de inscripciones gratuitas.","Porque escribir un cuento tambi\xe9n es una forma de sembrar futuro, y responder al llamado de la Vida.","\uD83D\uDCDD Inscripciones libres durante toda la semana del D\xeda de la Tierra","\uD83C\uDF89 \xa1Es tu oportunidad de ser parte del Cuento Infinito!","Porque somos agua, somos bosque, somos vida."],"hasArticleButton":true,"articleButtonText":"Reg\xedstrate aqu\xed"},{"id":"minga-fest","className":"minga-fest","bannerTitle1":"Minga Mundial","bannerTitle2":"por el Ambiente","bannerSubtitle":"El llamado de la vida","hasBannerButton":true,"bannerButtonText":"Con\xf3ce m\xe1s","images":["/news/minga-fest/img1.png"],"date":"26 de abril, 2025","articleTitle":"Minga Mundial por el Ambiente","articleParagraphs":["El planeta est\xe1 atravesando una crisis ambiental que pone en grave riesgo las fuentes de agua, la biodiversidad, los bosques y la vida en la Tierra. Ante esta situaci\xf3n cr\xedtica, es imprescindible promover acciones masivas de educaci\xf3n y concientizaci\xf3n para resaltar la importancia de cuidar las fuentes de agua, reforestar con especies nativas, reciclar pl\xe1sticos y otros materiales que contaminan r\xedos y mares, y reducir los niveles de emisiones.","Minga - Fest 2025","La Minga - Fest 2025 se plantea como una acci\xf3n comunitaria global para limpiar fuentes de agua, reforestar y reciclar, que se llevar\xe1 a cabo de manera simult\xe1nea en todo el mundo los d\xedas 19 y 20 de abril de 2025. Esta celebraci\xf3n de la naturaleza integra actividades educativas, rituales, m\xfasica, arte, investigaci\xf3n e incidencia ciudadana, creando un momento inmersivo y vivencial de conexi\xf3n con la Madre Tierra.","El evento rescata el concepto de la minga, una pr\xe1ctica ancestral de los pueblos ind\xedgenas que simboliza la acci\xf3n comunitaria en beneficio del bien colectivo. A trav\xe9s de estas acciones, se busca fomentar una conciencia ambiental global y una relaci\xf3n m\xe1s respetuosa y sostenible con nuestro entorno natural."],"hasArticleButton":true,"articleButtonText":"Inscr\xedbete haciendo click aqu\xed"},{"id":"campana-educativa-cuidado-del-agua","className":"campana-educativa-cuidado-del-agua","bannerTitle1":"Arcandina y Rotary:","bannerTitle2":"Campa\xf1a Educativa","bannerSubtitle":"Concientizaci\xf3n sobre el Cuidado del Agua","hasBannerButton":false,"bannerButtonText":"","bannerButtonLink":"","images":["/news/campa\xf1a-educativa/img1.webp"],"date":"04 de diciembre, 2024","articleTitle":"Arcandina y Rotary lanzan la campa\xf1a educativa sobre el cuidado del agua","articleParagraphs":["La situaci\xf3n ambiental y la sequ\xeda que vive el pa\xeds demanda acciones ciudadanas para promover una cultura orientada hacia el buen uso del agua. Frente a esta necesidad, Fundaci\xf3n Arcandina junto con el Club Rotario Los Chillos Milenio, lanzan la campa\xf1a: Historias para Cuidar el Agua, que incluye una miniserie con los personajes de Arcandina, con temas para cuidar los r\xedos, p\xe1ramos, quebradas y evitar la contaminaci\xf3n del agua.","La campa\xf1a se orienta a fortalecer la conciencia ambiental a trav\xe9s de elementos l\xfadicos y la educomunicaci\xf3n basada en valores, promoviendo la formaci\xf3n de agentes de cambio. Los mensajes a trav\xe9s de los personajes Arcandina son el veh\xedculo para crear empat\xeda hacia la naturaleza y fortalecer la resiliencia.","Fundaci\xf3n Arcandina tiene una reconocida experiencia y trayectoria en educaci\xf3n ambiental, desde 1997 ha producido programas de televisi\xf3n, videos, campa\xf1as y material did\xe1ctico que han llegado a m\xe1s de 6 millones de ni\xf1os en el continente. Ha recibido reconocimientos de la UNESCO, la National Wildlife Federation y el Municipio de Quito, entre otros","La campa\xf1a se implementa en escuelas y redes sociales con el apoyo del Rotary Club los Chillos Milenio y ha beneficiado a m\xe1s de 2.800 estudiantes.","Contacto: Pablo Palacios-Arcandina 0963089303","Alejandra Lozada: Rotary Club 0992567278"],"hasArticleButton":false,"articleButtonText":"","articleButtonLink":""},{"id":"condecoracion-maria-elena-ordo\xf1ez","className":"","bannerTitle1":"Mar\xeda Elena Ord\xf3\xf1ez:","bannerTitle2":"Reconocida por su legado educativo","bannerSubtitle":"Un homenaje a su aporte a la televisi\xf3n infantil y la conciencia ambiental","hasBannerButton":true,"bannerButtonText":"Con\xf3ce m\xe1s","images":["/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img1.webp","/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img2.webp","/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img3.webp","/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img4.webp","/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img5.webp"],"date":"06 de diciembre, 2024","articleTitle":"Mar\xeda Elena Ord\xf3\xf1ez es condecorada por el Municipio de Quito por su destacada labor en educaci\xf3n y valores ambientales","articleParagraphs":["Mar\xeda Elena Ord\xf3\xf1ez, creadora de Arcandina recibe condecoraci\xf3n del  Concejo del Municipio  Quito, en reconocimiento por su aporte a la literatura, la educaci\xf3n y la promoci\xf3n de la televisi\xf3n infantil de calidad.","En 1997, Mar\xeda Elena cre\xf3, junto al cineasta y escritor Pablo Palacios, el programa de televisi\xf3n Arcandina, la serie educativa m\xe1s trascendental de la televisi\xf3n ecuatoriana, que super\xf3 las fronteras del pa\xeds, llevando con orgullo la imagen de Ecuador a Am\xe9rica Latina y Estados Unidos., en cadenas como Telemundo y Azteca Am\xe9rica. Con el tiempo, Arcandina se convirti\xf3 en un programa emblem\xe1tico de la familia quite\xf1a, contribuyendo a la formaci\xf3n de una cultura ambiental en varias generaciones.","Mar\xeda Elena ha dedicado su vida al servicio de la educaci\xf3n,   la literatura infantil, la escritura y producci\xf3n de guiones y programas de televisi\xf3n, a trav\xe9s de una labor pionera e innovadora con la serie Arcandina, que ha logrado transmitir de manera  creativa los valores del cuidado ambiental, sensibilizando a m\xe1s de 5 millones de ni\xf1os en Ecuador y otros pa\xedses de la regi\xf3n.","Investigaciones sobre el impacto educativo de Arcandina, realizadas por las universidades de Stanford y Johns Hopkins, validaron t\xe9cnicamente  la alta calidad educativa y art\xedstica de la serie y por ello, la Unesco, la National Wildlife Federation  y otras organizaciones reconocieron a Arcandina como el programa de educaci\xf3n ambiental m\xe1s innovador del continente."],"hasArticleButton":false,"articleButtonText":""}],"en":[{"id":"cuento-infinito","className":"cuento-infinito","bannerTitle1":"Debut of the","bannerTitle2":"Infinite Story","bannerSubtitle":"For the Global Minga for the Environment and Earth Day","hasBannerButton":true,"bannerButtonText":"Sign up here","images":["/news/cuento-infinito/img1.png"],"date":"April 25, 2025","articleTitle":"Debut of the Infinite Story ✨","articleParagraphs":["At Arcandina, we believe that the dreams of children have the power to inspire the world. Therefore, in the framework of the Global Minga for the Environment, we are excited to launch the Infinite Story, Arcandina The Call of Life.","\uD83D\uDCAB A collective story, without an ending, inspired by the stories of Arcandina and continued by stories created by children and families from around the world who want to share how they care for nature, plant water, and defend life.","To celebrate Earth Day, we open a whole week of free registrations.","Because writing a story is also a way to plant a future and respond to the call of Life.","\uD83D\uDCDD Free registrations during the entire week of Earth Day","\uD83C\uDF89 This is your chance to be part of the Infinite Story!","Because we are water, we are forest, we are life."],"hasArticleButton":true,"articleButtonText":"Sign up here"},{"id":"minga-fest","className":"minga-fest","bannerTitle1":"Global Minga","bannerTitle2":"for the Environment","bannerSubtitle":"The Call of Life","hasBannerButton":true,"bannerButtonText":"Learn More","images":["/news/minga-fest/img1.png"],"date":"April 26, 2025","articleTitle":"Global Minga for the Environment","articleParagraphs":["The planet is facing an environmental crisis that seriously endangers water sources, biodiversity, forests, and life on Earth. In response to this critical situation, it is essential to promote massive education and awareness campaigns to highlight the importance of protecting water sources, reforesting with native species, recycling plastics and other materials that pollute rivers and oceans, and reducing emission levels.","Minga - Fest 2025","Minga - Fest 2025 is envisioned as a global community action to clean water sources, reforest, and recycle, taking place simultaneously around the world on April 19 and 20, 2025. This celebration of nature integrates educational activities, rituals, music, art, research, and citizen advocacy, creating an immersive and experiential moment of connection with Mother Earth.","The event embraces the concept of the \'minga,\' an ancestral practice of indigenous peoples that represents community action for the collective good. Through these actions, the aim is to foster global environmental awareness and a more respectful and sustainable relationship with our natural environment."],"hasArticleButton":true,"articleButtonText":"Sign up by clicking here"},{"id":"campana-educativa-cuidado-del-agua","className":"campana-educativa-cuidado-del-agua","bannerTitle1":"Arcandina and Rotary:","bannerTitle2":"Educational Campaign","bannerSubtitle":"Awareness on Water Care","hasBannerButton":false,"bannerButtonText":"","bannerButtonLink":"","images":["/news/campa\xf1a-educativa/img1.webp"],"date":"December 4, 2024","articleTitle":"Arcandina and Rotary Launch Educational Campaign on Water Care","articleParagraphs":["The environmental situation and drought in the country demand citizen actions to promote a culture focused on the responsible use of water. Addressing this need, the Arcandina Foundation, together with the Los Chillos Milenio Rotary Club, launched the campaign: Stories to Care for Water. The initiative includes a miniseries featuring Arcandina characters, highlighting themes about protecting rivers, p\xe1ramos, creeks, and preventing water pollution.","The campaign aims to strengthen environmental awareness through playful elements and educommunication based on values, promoting the formation of change agents. The messages delivered through the Arcandina characters serve as a vehicle to foster empathy for nature and build resilience.","The Arcandina Foundation has recognized expertise and experience in environmental education. Since 1997, it has produced television programs, videos, campaigns, and educational materials that have reached more than 6 million children across the continent. It has received accolades from UNESCO, the National Wildlife Federation, and the Municipality of Quito, among others.","The campaign is implemented in schools and on social media with the support of the Los Chillos Milenio Rotary Club and has benefited more than 2,800 students.","Contact: Pablo Palacios-Arcandina 0963089303","Alejandra Lozada: Rotary Club 0992567278"],"hasArticleButton":false,"articleButtonText":"","articleButtonLink":""},{"id":"condecoracion-maria-elena-ordo\xf1ez","className":"","bannerTitle1":"Mar\xeda Elena Ord\xf3\xf1ez:","bannerTitle2":"Recognized for Her Educational Legacy","bannerSubtitle":"A tribute to her contributions to children\'s television and environmental awareness","hasBannerButton":true,"bannerButtonText":"Learn More","images":["/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img1.webp","/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img2.webp","/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img3.webp","/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img4.webp","/news/condecoracion-maria-elena/img5.webp"],"date":"December 6, 2024","articleTitle":"Mar\xeda Elena Ord\xf3\xf1ez is Honored by the Municipality of Quito for Her Outstanding Work in Education and Environmental Values","articleParagraphs":["Mar\xeda Elena Ord\xf3\xf1ez, creator of Arcandina, is honored by the Council of the Municipality of Quito in recognition of her contributions to literature, education, and the promotion of high-quality children\'s television.","In 1997, Mar\xeda Elena, together with filmmaker and writer Pablo Palacios, created the television program Arcandina, the most influential educational series in Ecuadorian television history. It transcended national borders, proudly showcasing Ecuador’s image to Latin America and the United States on networks like Telemundo and Azteca Am\xe9rica. Over time, Arcandina became an iconic program for Quito families, contributing to the development of an environmental culture across multiple generations.","Mar\xeda Elena has dedicated her life to education, children’s literature, and the writing and production of television scripts and programs. Through pioneering and innovative work with the Arcandina series, she has creatively conveyed the values of environmental care, raising awareness among over 5 million children in Ecuador and other countries in the region.","Research on the educational impact of Arcandina, conducted by Stanford and Johns Hopkins universities, validated the series’ high educational and artistic quality. As a result, organizations such as UNESCO, the National Wildlife Federation, and others recognized Arcandina as the most innovative environmental education program on the continent."],"hasArticleButton":false,"articleButtonText":""}]}')}}]);